cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use auto-improve in your research, please cite it."
title: auto-improve
abstract: >-
  A GAN-style self-improvement loop for any text artifact. It mutates a file,
  grades each candidate with a separate judge model, runs a debiased pairwise
  keep/discard gate in both orderings, keeps only changes that genuinely win,
  and reverts the rest. The git branch improve/<tag> is the improvement log —
  every commit a verified gain.
type: software
authors:
